               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371211-name-169" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371211-name-169" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371211-name-169" type="surname" value="JENNINGS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371211-name-169" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN JENNINGS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a labourer. I went into the Bell, in the Uxbridge road, on the 4th of December—I was drunk—J had a hat and handkerchief—I went to sleep, and the hat and handkerchief were gone, and an old hat left in its place—this is my hat—the handkerchief was in it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371211-name-170" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371211-name-170" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371211-name-170" type="surname" value="CARTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371211-name-170" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES CARTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am potboy at this house. I saw the prisoner tike up this hat, and saw the handkerchief in it—the prosecutor was then asleep—he was not very drunk—the prisoner put the hat behind him, and took the handkerchief out—he looked at it, and put it back again behind him—the prosecutor awoke, and found out that his new hat was gone, and the old one left in its place.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
